-- Conformance tests for the Cons/Nil enum SeqLit shorthand on
-- user-defined Cons-shaped enums.
--
-- `var = ⟨a, b, c⟩` where `var` is enum-typed and the enum has a
-- 0-arity variant + a 2-arity self-recursive variant lowers to
-- `Cons(a, Cons(b, Cons(c, Nil)))`. After Phase 6.4 the runtime's
-- EffectList / ResultList / ArgList / StrList / IntList have all
-- moved to Seq(...); user-defined LinkedList-style enums are the
-- remaining Cons users, plus the runtime's PackedFieldList (which
-- gates on Seq-concatenation support; see plans/06-cons-removal).

import "stdlib/runtime.ev"

-- User-defined Cons/Nil enum
enum IntList = INil | ICons(Int, IntList)

claim sat_user_intlist
    nums ∈ IntList
    nums = ⟨10, 20, 30⟩
    nums = ICons(10, ICons(20, ICons(30, INil)))
